snippet.textDisplay:
Good day, dear friends!
‼from Russia
We are opening an urgent training camp, as the clinic is ready to receive us, and there is no time at all!
My name is Ilyusha, that's what Dad called me, I'm 1 year and 9 months old!
I'm a welcome child in the family, Mom says it's exactly what I dreamed of.
When I was 4 months old my parents began to notice that I was inactive, and at 6 months I lost all physical skills that I had, my hands became weak and my legs stopped listening to me!
On 4 June I was diagnosed with CMA type 1 (spinal muscular atrophy). The disease is caused by a breakage of the 7 exon gene, which is responsible for the production of protein, for the spinal motor neurons, which are responsible for muscle activity.
My motoneurons began to die, hence my weakness!
Over time, the disease will take away all my skills, as well as my ability to breathe, swallow... to live... My parents were told that I didn't have a chance to live and it would have been easier for them to have a "new" baby, but they chose a different path.
On August 29th I was able to get the world's first CMA SPINRAZA medicine, but unfortunately the treatment is lifelong! But that year a new drug was invented, after which I come back as if by the wave of a magic wand, the drug ZOLGENSMA.
The drug is injected once, but the cost is unthinkable = $2.4 million (~150 million rubles).
The amount is unrealistic, but if you sit and do nothing, then who can help me?! Except that there is very little time left, the drug is only up to 2 x years.
